  "description": [
    "10 JANUARY 7 1904 THE NEBRASKA INDEPENDENT f THE NEW PARTY Mr De Hurt Continues His Discussion Suffrage Money Tariff Editor Independent Negro slavery is dead The civil war killed it If the war didnt the 13th amendment did If the 13th amendment did not the 14th lid All persons born or naturalized in the United States bays the 14th amendment are citizens thereof This includes negroe3 The 13lh amendment gave them their freedom and the 14th made them citizens of the United States and of the state wherein they reside The 15th amendment prohibits any state lrom denying the right to vote on account of race color or previous condition of servitude This does not compel tne states to confer the right of suffrage hut it does prevent the states from de nying it on account of race color or previous condition of servitude In other words it compels the states to confer the right upon the blacks on j the same conditions as on whites This will open the way for an in telligent suffrage which will eventual ly give the southern states better laws than we have m the north What we want today north and south"
  ],
